text: Nassarius fissilabris is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae, the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks. ==Description== The shell size varies between 10 mm and 20 mm ==Distribution== This species is distributed in the Red Sea and along Oman. ==References== * Vine, P. (1986). Red Sea Invertebrates. Immel Publishing, London. 224 pp. ==External links== * Gastropods.com : Nassarius (Plicarcularia) fissilabrus; accessed : 31 December 2010 Category:Nassariidae Category:Gastropods described in 1852
